the importance of the "prompts"

00:01:41.600 --> 00:01:46.560
requirement; how to read a VPAT report skeptically;

00:01:46.560 --> 00:01:50.399
what to look for in a trustworthy
accessibility report;

00:01:50.399 --> 00:01:54.479
ATAGS unique extra conformance
requirements;

00:01:54.479 --> 00:02:00.880
why we should treat ATAG as required,
even when it's not explicitly listed in

00:02:00.880 --> 00:02:04.240
policy. 
The speaker of the session, Mitchell Evan,

00:02:04.240 --> 00:02:09.920
has coached design and development teams
for nine years, harnessing his ADHD

00:02:09.920 --> 00:02:14.800
creativity to achieve enterprise scale
accessibility through the power of

00:02:14.800 --> 00:02:21.040
authoring tools, UI frameworks, and design
systems. Most recently, he led the VPAT

00:02:21.040 --> 00:02:25.840
reporting practice at Level Access,
applying international accessibility

00:02:25.840 --> 00:02:34.720
standards, WCAG 2.1, Section 508, and EN 301
549 to the web application, native

00:02:34.720 --> 00:02:38.400
